<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.30.7-8_0001b" />
<note type="curatorial">116-2 Aly Collection</note>


<fw type="imprint">
<hi rend="caps">THE STANHOPE</hi> 
<lb/>
5th Ave. at 81st. St., <hi rend="caps">N. Y.</hi> 28 Telephone Butterfield 8-5800

Sharp Ltd. <figure/> Hotels
</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>Oct. 14, '60</dateline>



<salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Have had a most successful time here. The affair Wed. evening at the Annual <hi rend="underline">Westerners</hi> dinner was a real 
<hi rend="underline">smash</hi>. The response was surprising to me.

<fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.30.7-8_0001a"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>

I talked off-hand about Black Elk, and it was "one of those things" Some important people came out to see me, Mari Sandoz and Homer Croy among others.</p>

<p>I tried to get into the <hi rend="caps">U. N.</hi> yesterday, but police swarmed about the place.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.30.7-8_0002a"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

<p>Am leaving at 12:20 for Ithaca. Will talk there to classes on the 17th &amp; 18th. The public talk will be on Wed evening. Then I'll come back here for the flight home.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.30.7-8_0002b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>

<p>Macmillans sent a lady from the editorial dept to greet me. <hi rend="underline">Can't</hi> we induce you to give us another book?" I answered, "Tease me, I might."</p>
<closer>
<salute>Affectionately</salute>
<signed>John</signed>
</closer>

<fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
</div1>
